.nh
.TH "BCDOCK" "1" "Jan 2025" "BCDock CLI" "BCDock Manual"

.SH NAME
bcdock-config-list - List all available configurations (versions, countries, regions)


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbcdock config list [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
List all available BC configurations - versions, countries, and regions -
in one call. This command is not yet implemented.

.PP
Use these commands today:
  bcdock config regions              - Azure regions
  bcdock artifacts list --region  - BC versions + countries in a region
  bcdock artifacts countries         - country codes

.PP
Exit codes:
  1   general error (not yet implemented)


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for list


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--api-url\fP=""
	API base URL (env: BCDOCK_API_URL)

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colored output

.PP
\fB-o\fP, \fB--output\fP="table"
	Output format: table, json, csv

.PP
\fB-q\fP, \fB--quiet\fP[=false]
	Suppress non-essential output

.PP
\fB--timeout\fP=30s
	Request timeout

.PP
\fB--token\fP=""
	API token (env: BCDOCK_TOKEN)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  bcdock config regions
  bcdock artifacts list --region australiaeast --fast-only
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBbcdock-config(1)\fP
